robust() doesn't compute model-based tests (and it would be confusing if it does so for some special cases). If the QM test cannot be computed (for whatever reason), robust() is designed to catch this and issue a warning ("Could not obtain the cluster-robust omnibus Wald test (use verbose=TRUE for more details)." If one then decides to use the model-based test, one can then use the regular output from the model.

PS: Please always include the mailing list in replies.

Best,
Wolfgang

