In-Reply-To: <CA+dzWjqWCmKVKddWj14PGFULB2uHM7vEmUGT17C6U6P2wAs44w@mail.gmail.com>
References: <334b98885b608de4b64e21667934cada@posteo.de>
 <64f9724840154137a92bad6de05f92ac@UM-MAIL3214.unimaas.nl>
 <CA+dzWjrpCWtvS_BqO+Q8=mGnAyeYm5LaZs7V3qECsYWtanmP1w@mail.gmail.com>
 <8c4bb8b0de3f4a2aae65fab6fe693f9b@UM-MAIL3214.unimaas.nl>
 <CA+dzWjqWCmKVKddWj14PGFULB2uHM7vEmUGT17C6U6P2wAs44w@mail.gmail.com>
Message-ID: <6f58d0f4a9074befb44d104f5b29a7a2@UM-MAIL3214.unimaas.nl>

The residuals are not the same as the sampling errors. Yes, the sampling errors have variance v_ij, but the *observed residuals* have a different variance which depends on the model being fitted, since Var(y_ij - fitted_ij) = Var(y_ij) + Var(fitted_ij) - 2*Cov(yij,fitted_ij).

Best,
Wolfgang

